questions.text: "I find it difficult to relax when I see something that needs improvement or fixing."
"I feel strongly that fairness and justice should be upheld as a matter of principle."
"I tend to feel a moral obligation to meet higher standards than I expect from others."
"I feel unsettled when things don’t meet my standards of order and correctness."
"I feel an inner pressure to improve things and hold myself to a higher standard than I expect from others, even when no one is watching."
"I feel frustrated when things or people don’t live up to the standards I hold."

"I constantly notice flaws, inefficiencies, and ways things could be improved, and I feel a responsibility to fix them. It frustrates me when others don't seem to care about doing things the right way."
"I often neglect my own needs because I feel fulfilled when I’m making others feel loved and supported."
"I instinctively notice when someone needs support and feel drawn to help them, sometimes to the point of neglecting my own needs."
"I tend to feel hurt if my efforts to help others are not acknowledged."
"I often anticipate others’ needs before they even ask for help."
"I instinctively notice when someone needs support and feel drawn to help them."
"I feel a strong emotional need to be valued by the people I care about."
"I intuitively sense what others need and feel deeply fulfilled when I can help, but I wish others would notice what I need too. It’s hard for me to ask for help directly."
"I feel driven to succeed and fear being seen as incapable, unremarkable, or a failure."
"I often adjust my personality or behavior to match the expectations of others."
"I naturally detect what others value and scan for opportunities to shine and advance."
"I feel restless and unsatisfied if I’m not actively working toward something significant, or an ambitious goal."
"I measure my worth by how much I’m able to achieve. If I’m not achieving, I feel like I’m falling behind."
"I feel a strong sense of purpose when I’m being recognized for what I accomplish."
"I value efficiency and tangible results, and I don’t like wasting time on things that don’t move me forward. If something can be done better, faster, or more strategically, I’ll optimize it."
"I feel most alive when I’m expressing something that reflects my unique identity and emotional depth."
"I tend to feel like I don’t fully belong, as if there’s something missing or different about me."
"I find beauty and meaning in experiences that others might overlook as ordinary."
"I often feel a longing for something that is difficult to define, a sense that something important is missing."
"I dislike the idea of blending in with the crowd and look for ways to express my individuality."
"I seek the deeper emotional truth in every experience because raw, unfiltered feeling is what makes life meaningful to me."
"I experience emotions more intensely than most people, and I find deep meaning in beauty, art, and self-expression. Ordinary or surface-level things don’t fulfill me—I crave depth and authenticity."
"I feel a stronger need to gather as much knowledge as possible before making decisions than most people I know."
"I feel most at ease when I have the space to handle things on my own."
"I feel more comfortable observing from the sidelines than being the center of attention."
"I tend to feel drained when others make too many emotional or social demands on me."
"I worry about running out of energy or resources, so I carefully manage what I give to others."
"I prefer relationships with clear boundaries so I can maintain my personal space and autonomy."
""I need time alone to gather knowledge and process my thoughts before I feel ready to engage with the world."
"I prefer environments where I know who I can trust, and uncertainty or unclear expectations make me uneasy."
"I tend to seek reassurance from others to help me feel more confident in my decisions."
"I tend to look for signs that people or systems are trustworthy before I fully commit."
"I frequently worry about potential risks and plan for worst-case scenarios."
"I feel more confident when I have clear guidelines or authority to rely on."
"I feel most at ease when I can rely on others to be consistent and dependable."

"I constantly scan for risks, inconsistencies, or things that could go wrong because I want to be prepared for anything. I don’t like feeling blindsided, so I think through every possibility in advance."
"I crave new experiences and feel stifled by the same routine. I need variety and stimulation to stay engaged."
"I feel energized by imagining exciting new ideas and experiences that I can pursue in the future."
"I always look for opportunities to make life more fun, enjoyable, and full of variety."
"I feel trapped and restless when I’m stuck in a routine or restricted environment."
"I value flexibility and prefer to do things my way. I don’t want to feel trapped or limited by someone else’s plan."
"I avoid dwelling on negative emotions and prefer to stay optimistic."
"I don’t just seek happiness—I crave a feeling of aliveness, a sense that I’m making the most of every moment."
"I pride myself on being strong and independent, and I rarely let others see when I’m feeling vulnerable."
"I naturally assess who is strong, who is weak, and who is in control in any situation."
"I tend to take charge in situations where I feel things are out of control, to protect myself and others."
"I dislike relying on others and prefer to be in control of my own decisions and resources."
"I don’t hesitate to confront and call out unfairness directly, even if it makes others uncomfortable."
"I respect people who are strong and direct, even if we don’t always agree."
"I take charge naturally because I trust my instincts and don’t see the point in waiting for permission to act. If something needs to get done, I make sure it happens."
"I tend to agree with others to avoid arguments, even if I feel differently."
"I feel most comfortable when everything around me is calm and harmonious."
"I tend to lose track of my own needs because I prioritize keeping peace and avoiding conflict."
"I sometimes go along with others’ preferences to avoid making waves or drawing attention to myself."
"I value maintaining stability and avoiding unnecessary disruptions"
"I prefer a calm, conflict-free environment over one filled with excitement, intensity, or drama."
"I often merge with the people around me, easily seeing their perspectives and going along with what they want."
